FBIS4-41198 "drsov121_d_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 Regional Affairs Panel To Draft Treaty With Bashkortostan Named Panel To Draft Treaty With Bashkortostan Named PM2306095194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 22 Jun 94 First Edition p 4 PM2306095194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Russian Federation Presidential Directive No. 300-d, signed by President Yeltsin and dated 14 June 1994] [Text] A commission to draw up a draft bilateral treaty on the demarcation of areas of responsibility [predmety vedeniya] and the reciprocal delegation of powers between organs of state power in the Russian Federation and the Republic of Bashkortostan is to be set up with the following members: S.M. Shakhray, deputy chairman of the Russian Federation Government, commission leader; R.G. Abdulatipov, deputy chairman of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly Federation Council (by agreement) [po soglasovaniyu]; S.A. Shapovalov, chairman of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly State Duma Committee for Federation Affairs and Regional Policy (by agreement); A.G. Shapovalyants, Russian Federation deputy minister of economics; A.M. Pozdnyakov, Russian Federation deputy minister for nationalities affairs and regional policy; A.V. Maslov, deputy head of the Russian Federation president's State Legal Administration; A.P. Kozlov, head of the Russian Federation Government Apparatus's Department for Cooperation with Russian Federation Regions; V.A. Pechenev, deputy head of the Russian Federation Presidential Staff Administration for Work with the Territories. [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin [Dated] 14 June 1994 No. 300-d
